name.description: A unique identifier describing the queue

pricingPlan.description: Specifies whether the pricing plan for the queue is on-demand or reserved. Valid values are `ON_DEMAND` or `RESERVED`. Default to `ON_DEMAND`.

reservationPlanSettings.description: A detail pricing plan of the  reserved queue. See below.

status.description: A status of the queue. Valid values are `ACTIVE` or `RESERVED`. Default to `PAUSED`.

tags.description: A map of tags to assign to the resource. .If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
